Linking and summarization rules

- When Stack documentation depends on protocol-level mechanics:
  - Link to the relevant Protocol documentation.
  - Provide a brief operator-oriented summary (1–2 sentences).
  - Do not duplicate full protocol explanations.

- Prefer linking over copying when the content is explanatory rather than operational.

Moving and restructuring content

- Content may be moved or reorganized within docs/stack/* to improve clarity and correctness.
- Preserve meaning exactly when moving or restructuring.
- Update internal links to reflect new locations.
- Do not change URLs unless necessary.
- If a URL must change, add appropriate redirects
- Never add redirects that impact docs/network/.

Operator-first constraints

- Assume the reader is a competent technical operator, not an end user.
- Optimize for safe execution, clear responsibility boundaries, and failure awareness.
- Explicitly state assumptions, prerequisites, and failure modes when present in source material.
- Avoid marketing language or value claims unless they are already explicit in the source.

Quality bar

Every page introduced or modified in Linea Stack must satisfy all of the following:

- The reader can clearly tell whether the page is explanatory, instructional, or capability-focused.
- No operational steps rely on undocumented or inferred behavior.
- All technical claims are traceable to source material or linked Protocol documentation.
- Missing critical information is surfaced explicitly via TODO metadata, not hidden in prose.
- Besu documentation is a good quality standard. A user can operate a node by following the clear consise details: https://besu.hyperledger.org/
- OP documentation https://docs.optimism.io/op-stack/protocol/getting-started is a good quality standard for the high-level "How it works" items (however is bad quality in terms of diataxis structure)
- ZK sync docs share a similar docs structure standard: https://docs.zksync.io/ however, the trust assumptions of their users is far lower than linea, so they are not considered good quality standard

